RingZip bundles a trimmed copy of LMMs-Eval, used to reproduce the paper's
experiments.

  Upstream : https://github.com/EvolvingLMMs-Lab/lmms-eval
  Version  : 0.5.0
  License  : MIT (see lmms_eval/LICENSE)

Changes from upstream
---------------------
  * Models: kept only the Qwen2.5-VL family used in the paper — the base model,
    RingZip (qwen2_5_vl_coherence[_pma]), and the compared baselines
    (FastV, VisionZip, DivPrune, DUET, IVC-Prune). All other model adapters
    were removed.
  * Tasks: kept only XLRS-Bench (xlrs), LRS-VQA, and MME-RealWorld-RS; all other
    benchmarks were removed. The lrs_vqa and mme_realworld task code is modified
    from upstream to match the official benchmark protocols (metrics, prompts,
    max_new_tokens).
  * qwen2_5_vl_coherence imports the compressor from the standalone `ringzip`
    package instead of the in-tree _coherence_core.py.
